<TITLE> Bangladesh condemns Islamabad blast </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sect 20 (bdnews24.com) - Foreign adviser Iftekhar Ahmed Chowdhury condemned the bomb blasts in Islamabad that killed at least 17 people on Saturday. Chowdhury termed the attack a cowardly act of terrorism and said "such attack will bring no benefit for the perpetrators." In his instant reaction, the adviser said: "The people of Bangladesh stand by the people and the government of Pakistan at this hour." He expressed deep shock at the loss of innocent lives. bd
